==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: polycosmic
<hw>pol`y*cos"mic</hw> <pr>(p⟦ocr⟧l`⟦esl⟧*k⟦ocr⟧z"m⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + <ets>cosmic</ets>, containing
many universes. (<fu>2003</fu>).]</ety> <fld>(Computers)</fld>
<def>Representing multiple possible worlds; -- used of a computational
ontology that includes logically inconsistent assertions (theories),
structured as different possible worlds; <as>as, the only way to
accommodate different theories of physics in one ontology is for that
ontology to be <ex>polycosmic</ex></as>.</def> <note>A computational
ontology that includes both the existence of one God and nonexistence of
God as alternative and inconsistent theories would be
<ex>polycosmic</ex></note>.⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polycotyledon</ent>⟦br⟧
